    public interface Interruptable
    An interface for interruption of long running computational tasks.

    Nikolay Ognyanov

      • interrupt

        void interrupt()
        Interrupts this task.

      • isInterrupted

        boolean isInterrupted()
        Tests whether this task has been interrupted. The interrupted status of the task is unaffected by this method.
        Returns:
        true if this task has been interrupted; false otherwise.

      • interrupted

        boolean interrupted()
        Tests whether this task has been interrupted. The interrupted status of the task is cleared.
        Returns:
        true if this thread has been interrupted; false otherwise.
